title: New City, NY: Rockland County: Stop Project Maple!
description:
Join us at the Rockland County Legislature meeting to call on the board to pass a resolution against Project Maple — a dangerous fracked gas pipeline expansion plan that threatens our climate, our air, and our health.

Fossil fuel company Enbridge's Project Maple would expand the amount of fracked gas running through the existing Algonquin Pipeline (which runs through Rockland County) by replacing existing pipe, extending the pipeline, and expanding the Stony Point compressor station.

This project would lock us into decades of fossil fuel dependence — just when we need to be transitioning to clean energy. It’s risky, unnecessary, and completely out of step with New York’s climate goals. By passing a resolution calling on Governor Hochul to deny permits for this pipeline expansion, Rockland County will be a climate leader opposing this dirty, harmful project. 

Meet us at the Legislative Building, where we’ll give public comments about the importance of Rockland County passing a resolution against Project Maple. If you haven't made public comments before, no worries! We will prepare you.

Let’s pack the room and show our elected officials that Rockland County stands against pipeline expansions! Bring your friends, your voice, and your passion — we’ll have talking points ready to go!

Citi Bikes and bike rentals from Blazing Saddles will be available on Governor's Island. Please contact emily.jacobi@transalt.org to let us know if will be needing a bike rental.

description:
Voting rights have been under attack at the federal level over the past few years. A 2013 Supreme Court decision gutted the federal Voting Rights Act, and now a proposed bill in Congress, the so-called “Safeguard American Voter Eligibility (SAVE) Act”, would disenfranchise millions of voters across the country by demanding proof of citizenship before they can register to vote. Turning this into law would be a logistical nightmare: fewer than half of American adults have a valid passport, and millions can’t easily access their paper birth certificate. This isn’t just red tape–it’s voter suppression. 

Join our webinar to learn more about how New Jersey can fight back by protecting and expanding our voting rights, including by passing the John R. Lewis Voter Empowerment Act of New Jersey. Join advocates and the bill sponsor, Assemblywoman Verlina Reynolds-Jackson, to learn how you  take the first steps needed to protect our democracy.
